Continental Air's Parent
   To File Chapter 11 Plan
That arrangement will make the creditors' group the
company's new shareholders. It also is expected to reduce
significantly Continental's sizable long-term debt.
   The airline had the exclusive right to file its
reorganization plan until last November, but asked the
bankruptcy judge overseeing the case to give it more time to
come to a consensual plan with its creditors. That deadline
expires at the end of today.